    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Units will exit the repair pad in the direction of the rallypoint, so if that cell is blocked, they won't leave. To prevent that, I usually set the rallypoint to the opposite direction of the front lint (ie. opposite from the direction where damaged units would most probably approach from) immediately after placing a repair pad.\n\nHowever, we could of course try other exits when the immediately obvious one is blocked. That doesn't currently happen.\n"
